Hmm, I think that must be happening in the swift backend rather than the crypt remote because of the low level retries (the crypt backed doesn't do low level retries).

Can you try

    rclone lsf secret:/ -vv --dump bodies --low-level-retries 1 --retries 1

And post the output please? (Redact as necessary).

What happens if you do this - does it do the same thing?

    rclone lsf home_storage_backup_ovh_pci:home_storage_backup

Can you post the output of

    rclone lsf home_storage_backup_ovh_pci:home_storage_backup -vv --dump bodies --low-level-retries 1 --retries 1

Thanks

This is the problem

> GET /v1/AUTH_xxx/home_storage_backup/home_storage_backup?delimiter=%2F&format=json&limit=1000 HTTP/1.1

Just provides an empty body.

Whereas when I try that on a different provider on an empty container

I get

> GET /v1/AUTH_XXXX/issue-3890?format=json&limit=1000 HTTP/1.1

the body response being

```
[]
```

I tried this on two different Openstack providers and it gave that result.

So I think this is a bug in the OVH implementation!

Here is what the response should look like: https://docs.openstack.org/api-ref/object-store/?expanded=show-container-details-and-list-objects-detail#response-example-format-json

Note that an empty string isn't a valid JSON array.

You can probably work around this by uploading a single file.

I was able to solve that by using the v3 endpoint instead of v2

New config (`secret` remote is unchanged):
```
[home_storage_backup_ovh_pci]
type = swift
env_auth = false
auth_version = 3
auth = https://auth.cloud.ovh.net/v3/
endpoint_type = public
tenant_domain = default
tenant = xxx
domain = default
user = xxx
```
All actions (copy / sync / lsf / lsd) are fine now.

Glad you've figured it out :-)

Do you think we should adjust the default endpoint in the rclone configurator?

```
 6 / OVH

```
